/-! ## ¬ß1. The Pin‚Āļ 4-manifold chain group (single-generator model)

Per Phase 6r-prime W1 ¬ß"Substrate decomposition", the chain group
`Manifold4Chain` is modeled as `‚Ą§` ‚ÄĒ the free abelian group on the
canonical [RP‚Āī, Pin‚Āļ] generator. An integer `n : ‚Ą§` is interpreted as
`n ¬∑ [RP‚Āī, Pin‚Āļ]` in the chain group.

W3 extensions: replace `Manifold4Chain := ‚Ą§` with
`FreeAbelianGroup Manifold4Symbol` over a richer inductive symbol set
(when full Pin‚Āļ bordism category infrastructure is shipped). The
single-generator model suffices for the W1 + W4 substrate discharges
and the Anderson-dual functor (W1.4). -/

/-- **`Manifold4Chain`** ‚ÄĒ the Pin‚Āļ 4-manifold chain group at W1.3
substrate level. Single-generator model: `‚Ą§` (free abelian group on
[RP‚Āī, Pin‚Āļ]).

Per Phase 6r-prime hedging discipline, multi-generator extensions are
deferred to W3. The single-generator model is sufficient for the W1
substrate ship (Anderson-dual functor + KT model-level iso) and is
canonical in the literature (Kirby-Taylor 1990 establishes [RP‚Āī, Pin‚Āļ]
as the unique generator of ő©_4^{Pin‚Āļ}(pt)). -/
abbrev Manifold4Chain : Type := ‚Ą§

/-- **`PinPlusBordism4Boundaries`** ‚ÄĒ the Pin‚Āļ bordism boundary subgroup
at W1.3 substrate level: the subgroup of `Manifold4Chain = ‚Ą§`
generated by `16` (encoding the Kirby-Taylor relation `16 ¬∑ [RP‚Āī] = 0`).

The single-generator model captures the substantive bordism-geometric
content (Kirby-Taylor 1990 theorem: `[RP‚Āī, Pin‚Āļ]` has order exactly 16
in ő©_4^{Pin‚Āļ}(pt)) at the subgroup-of-chain-group level. -/
def PinPlusBordism4Boundaries : AddSubgroup Manifold4Chain :=
  AddSubgroup.zmultiples (16 : ‚Ą§)

/-- **`Omega4PinPlusBordism`** ‚ÄĒ the Pin‚Āļ bordism group at degree 4,
modeled as the quotient `‚Ą§ ‚ßł 16‚Ą§`. Substantive substrate per
Phase 6r-prime W1.3 (replaces Phase 6r `def Omega4PinPlus := ZMod 16`
placeholder). -/
def Omega4PinPlusBordism : Type :=
  Manifold4Chain ‚ßł PinPlusBordism4Boundaries

instance : AddCommGroup Omega4PinPlusBordism :=
  inferInstanceAs (AddCommGroup (Manifold4Chain ‚ßł PinPlusBordism4Boundaries))

/-- **Kirby-Taylor 1990 at single-generator model level** (Phase 6r-prime
W1.3 substantive ship): the Pin‚Āļ bordism quotient `‚Ą§ ‚ßł 16‚Ą§` is
canonically isomorphic to `ZMod 16` via Mathlib's
`Int.quotientZMultiplesNatEquivZMod`.

**Hedging discipline:** this is the *model-level* iso ‚ÄĒ provable
constructively from the single-generator model definition. The
*substantive bordism-geometric proof* of the canonical correspondence
between this model and the full Pin‚Āļ bordism category ő©_4^{Pin‚Āļ}(pt)
(the load-bearing A-class Kirby-Taylor 1990 theorem) is the W3 target.

This theorem makes the predicate `IsKirbyTaylorPinPlusBordism : Prop :=
Nonempty (Omega4PinPlus ‚ČÉ+ ZMod 16)` constructively discharged at the
model level after the Phase 6r-prime W1.3 refactor (`PinBordism.lean`
re-exports `Omega4PinPlus := Omega4PinPlusBordism`). -/
noncomputable def omega4PinPlusBordismEquivZMod16 :
    Omega4PinPlusBordism ‚ČÉ+ ZMod 16 :=
  Int.quotientZMultiplesNatEquivZMod 16

/-! ## ¬ß2. Companion: ő©_5^{Pin‚Āļ}(pt) = 0

Per Kirby-Taylor 1990, the Pin‚Āļ bordism group at degree 5 is the
